{
  "texts": [
    "The ∇ x t log p(x t) term is referred to as the score function [47].",
    "It is the gradient of the log-probability of the diffused data.",
    "The solution for the reverse SDE has the same marginal probabilities p(x t) as the forward SDE.",
    "Alternatively, instead of generating new samples using the reverse SDE, there exists a deterministic ordinary differential equation (ODE) which preserves p(x t).",
    "This is called the probability-flow ODE [38], and is given bydx t = - 1 2 β(t) x t + ∇ x t log p(x t) dt."
  ]
}